title: For Sale/Trade:  NOS (New old stock) Polish AKMS / AK47 Underfolder
postcontent:
If you are not familiar with these rifles, please do a little research before making a low offer and then comparing it to a CAI, PAP, WASR, AMD or something else along those lines. This is a premium Polish AK47. These rifles are built on AKM stamped receivers 7.62x39mm rifle,  from a numbers matching unissued Radom (Circle 11) kits with original chromelined barrel, on a Nodak NDS-3 receiver. All parts have been finished to match and are in excellent+ condition. This gun is new from the American builder and comes with 1 military magazine. 
 Radom in Poland has been known for over half a century for producing some of the highest quality AK type rifles, in terms of fit and finish. The factory began by making the milled AK47, before moving on to the stamped AKM and AKMS series. These were themselves replaced by the Tantal and now Beryl. 
 In 2005, the US gov't decided to no longer allow parts kits to come in, with original barrels intact. So for the past half decade, all kits have had cut up barrels and builders have been forced to use various American substitutes. This is why nearly all other AK's on the market have non-chrome-lined or non original chrome-lined barrels. 
 These rifles were professionally built from a kit imported back when original barrels were allowed. So this rifle features a Cold Hammer Forged and chrome-lined 16.25" piece manufactured by Radom. Serials match with this kit and it was built up on a Nodak Spud NDS-3 receiver by Allied Armament. The US 922(r) parts are: receiver, trigger group, slant brake, and polymer pistol grip. This rifle can accept any handguard, buttstock, and pistol grip designed to fit a stamped receiver AKM/AK74.

Beyond this, the Polish rifles feature the best and smoothest operating parts out there. These rifles are not being made anymore. There are a few out there that might function as well such as Arsenal but none quite as collectible. $1,250 includes a hard case and one magazine.
